<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1052,1077]" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">Comments:</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1865" box="[348,494,1052,1077]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[348,494,1052,1077]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">Brachymetra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a small and strictly Neotropical genus represented by four species in 
<collectingRegion box="[1354,1436,1052,1077]" country="Paraguay" name="Central" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">Central</collectingRegion>
America: 
<taxonomicName authority="(Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843)" authorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" authorityYear="1843" baseAuthorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[264,722,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albinervus">
<emphasis box="[264,415,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">B. albinervus</emphasis>
(Amyot &amp; Serville, 1843)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hungerford &amp; Matsuda, 1957" authorityName="Hungerford &amp; Matsuda" authorityYear="1957" box="[736,1186,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shawi">
<emphasis box="[736,834,1087,1112]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">B. shawi</emphasis>
Hungerford &amp; Matsuda, 1957
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Shaw, 1933" authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1933" box="[1199,1432,1087,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unca">
<emphasis box="[1199,1287,1089,1112]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">B. unca</emphasis>
Shaw, 1933
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Cordeiro" authorityName="Pacheco-Chaves &amp; Cordeiro &amp; Moreira &amp; Springer" authorityYear="2018" box="[199,434,1124,1149]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bernaldi" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[199,325,1124,1149]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">B. bernaldi</emphasis>
Cordeiro
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[447,537,1124,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[447,537,1124,1149]" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
Among these, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Shaw" authorityYear="1933" box="[708,794,1125,1148]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="unca">
<emphasis box="[708,794,1125,1148]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">B. unca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is easily recognized by antennomere I longer than II and 
<collectionCode box="[151,179,1161,1184]" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">III</collectionCode>
together, and the pronotum with the longitudinal midline dark brown, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hungerford &amp; Matsuda" authorityYear="1957" box="[1069,1165,1159,1184]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="shawi">
<emphasis box="[1069,1165,1159,1184]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">B. shawi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be identified by the pronotum with an acute apex, reaching to abdominal mediotergite I in apterous forms and extending well beyond the suture between meso- and metanota in alate individuals, and the fore femur without conical black setae ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,151,1581]" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">
The new species is more similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[596,746,1303,1328]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albinervus">
<emphasis box="[596,746,1303,1328]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">B. albinervus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, with which it shares the general color and body proportions. However, it differs from it by the weak median carina of the pronotum in alate individuals; and males with abdominal mediotergite I with weak lateral notches, mediotergite VII quadrate, abdominal segment VIII in natural position almost entirely inserted into the abdominal cavity, and paramere narrow with apex acute. In 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Amyot &amp; Serville" baseAuthorityYear="1843" box="[1280,1429,1412,1437]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albinervus">
<emphasis box="[1280,1429,1412,1437]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">B. albinervus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the median carina of the pronotum and the lateral notches of abdominal tergum I are stronger; and males with abdominal mediotergite VII trapezoidal, abdominal segment VIII has at least half of its length exposed, and the paramere is wider with apex obtuse. All species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Mayr" authorityYear="1865" box="[720,866,1519,1544]" class="Insecta" family="Gerridae" genus="Brachymetra" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="495" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[720,866,1519,1544]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="495">Brachymetra</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
will be included in a forthcoming key and revision of the genus.
</paragraph>
